Processing WritingsController#update (for 127.0.0.1 at 2010-06-12 14:49:44) [PUT]
  Parameters: {"authenticity_token"=>"WIM8DMBpaTUoiy6P1XhqUKxwgXgkBZ704lNeTxGJQ8I=", "writing"=>{"author"=>"1", "linkText"=>"about_me", "date"=>"2008-01-02 07:21:07", "text"=>"### About Me: My name is Robert Carpenter.\r\n<img src=\"/images/robert.png\" alt=\"Robert Carpenter\" style=\"float:right; padding:22px;\" />\r\n#### I am a Christian.\r\n\r\nI choose not this path for happiness or some release from the day to day drone that occurs in society today. I don't believe in a fluffy religion that claims to take all problems away. But I do believe in an all powerful God. A God who died a horrible death for the forgiveness of sins.\r\n\r\nI try and live my life for God because I cant see the point in pouring myself fully into the things that I know to be only temporary.\r\n\r\n#### My beliefs are (crudely) summed up like this:\r\n\r\n * God exists and is perfect, omnipresent, omnipotent, entirely sovereign, and infinite among other things.\r\n * From the beginning God's law has existed and since the fall of Adam we have not been able to satisfy the requirements of that law.\r\n * I am (and we all are) incapable of living a life that fulfills the requirements of Gods law.\r\n * Knowing this God sent His only Son to the earth to be the only fully perfect man. This man, Jesus Christ, lived a perfect and sinless life according to Gods Law and then died a most painful death, suffering the complete loneliness of sin, so that we may be forgiven.\r\n * In order to attain eternal life, we must accept Jesus' payment for our sins.\r\nHere are some things that I am.\r\n\r\n####I am a Musician.\r\n\r\nI have been playing percussion for about 12 years and now have just over 5 years expirence singing in choir. I am currently working on learning piano, though it is proving difficult to do without a piano in the house to practice on.  I am going to learn guitar someday....\r\n\r\n####I am a Scholar.\r\n\r\nLearning is something that rings deep within my heart. I don't think that I have found a subject that I didn't want to learn. More than just learning I enjoy teaching people what I have learned and discussing the possibilities with people of all sorts.\r\n\r\nI recently graduated from [Fort Lewis College](http://www.fortlewis.edu) with a Bachelor of the Arts degree in Computer Science.  Currently I am a teacher and \"technology expert\" at a private Christian middle/high school.\r\n\r\n### About this website:\r\n\r\nThis website is my personal corner of the web.  You may think it silly, but I hand-coded it from the ground up.  I just like to be in control of my own source code.\r\n", "parseMarkdown"=>"1"}, "commit"=>"Update", "id"=>"77"}
